<li>However, you can effectively do the same thing by authorizing more students beyond the enrollment cap.</li>
<li>For example, if the enrollment cap for a class is currently set at 30, and you want to allow 35 students in the&nbsp;class, just keep authorizing students to add, until you've reached 35.</li>
<li>&nbsp;To learn how to authorize a student to add a class, view the Authorization Add tutorial.</li>
